To install on a fresh copy of Ubuntu:

I. Extract items in tar file to some location: /root/dir/path/to/thyrosim

II. Install c compiler:
$ sudo apt-get install linux-kernel-headers
$ sudo apt-get install build-essential

III. Install JSON::Syck
$ sudo cpan
cpan[1]>_ install JSON::Syck

IV. Install odepkg (odepkg-0.8.2.tar.gz included in thyrosim/octave)
$ octave --version
GNU Octave, version 3.2.4
Make sure to get the header that matches your octave version, although
odepkg requires Octave ver. >= 3.2.0
$ sudo apt-get install octave3.2-headers
$ cd thyrosim/octave (where odepkg-0.8.2.tar.gz is)
$ sudo octave
octave:1> pkg install odepkg-0.8.2.tar.gz
If there are permission issues, find where odepkg is install:
octave:1> pkg list
cd to the directory and make all m files executable
sudo chmod +x *.m

V. Setup Apache
httpd.conf:
For Ubuntu, /etc/apache2/httpd.conf

NameVirtualHost *:80

<VirtualHost *:80>
        DocumentRoot /root/dir
        ServerAdmin webmaster@example.com
        ServerName example.com
        ServerAlias *.example.com

        <Directory /root/dir/>
                Options FollowSymLinks -Indexes
                AllowOverride All
        </Directory>
        <Directory /root/dir/path/to/thyrosim/>
                Options FollowSymLinks -Indexes
                AllowOverride None
        </Directory>
        <Directory /root/dir/path/to/thyrosim/cgi-bin>
                Options ExecCGI
                AddHandler cgi-script .cgi
        </Directory>
</VirtualHost>

ports.conf:
Add: Listen your.ip.xxx.xxx
Comment out: Listen 80

VI. Common Errors:
Octave dies due to step size error: go into ~/octave/getinit.m and change
'InitialStep' from 10 to 1.
